    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "makes sense. so if a client wants to wear something more traditional—like a high-quality silk sari in india or a bespoke agbada in nigeria—for a formal business event, would that be considered \"sophisticated\" and \"professional\" in the same way a suit is? or would that be seen more as \"cultural attire\" rather than standard professional wear?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
